Subject: scsi: smartpqi: Add PCI ID for new ntcom controller
Patch-mainline: v5.15-rc1
Git-commit: e326b97c92ccbe0fa9256902ca0c20e2b6c40168
References: jsc#SLE-19728

Add support for Norsi ntcom Raid-24i controller:

    VID_0x9005, DID_0x028f, SVID_0x1dfc, SDID_0x3161

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20210714182847.50360-7-don.brace@microchip.com
Reviewed-by: Kevin Barnett <kevin.barnett@microchip.com>
Reviewed-by: Scott Benesh <scott.benesh@microchip.com>
Reviewed-by: Scott Teel <scott.teel@microchip.com>
Signed-off-by: Mike McGowen <mike.mcgowen@microchip.com>
Signed-off-by: Don Brace <don.brace@microchip.com>
Signed-off-by: Martin K. Petersen <martin.petersen@oracle.com>
Acked-by: Martin Wilck <mwilck@suse.com>
---
 drivers/scsi/smartpqi/smartpqi_init.c |    4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/scsi/smartpqi/smartpqi_init.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/smartpqi/smartpqi_init.c
@@ -9183,6 +9183,10 @@ static const struct pci_device_id pqi_pc
 	},
 	{
 		PCI_DEVICE_SUB(PCI_VENDOR_ID_ADAPTEC2, 0x028f,
+			       0x1dfc, 0x3161)
+	},
+	{
+		PCI_DEVICE_SUB(PCI_VENDOR_ID_ADAPTEC2, 0x028f,
 			       PCI_ANY_ID, PCI_ANY_ID)
 	},
 	{ 0 }
